## Scope

This packet documents the Congestion Mitigation and Air Quality
Improvement Program (CMAQ) emissions-reduction screen for each
candidate project produced by ClawModeler run `{{ run_id }}`. CMAQ is
authorized under 23 USC 149 and is the primary federal funding source
for transportation projects that reduce criteria-pollutant emissions
in designated nonattainment and maintenance areas. Screening follows
the FHWA *CMAQ Reference Guide* (current edition), which requires a
defensible per-pollutant emissions-reduction estimate (kilograms per
day) plus a cost-effectiveness value (USD per kilogram reduced),
grouped by the Reference Guide's eligibility categories.

## Methodology

Per the FHWA CMAQ Reference Guide, each candidate must attach:

- **Pollutant-specific kg/day reduction estimate** — the expected
  change in daily emissions for each applicable criteria pollutant
  (PM2.5, PM10, NOx, VOC, or CO), estimated via an approved method
  (EPA MOVES, CARB EMFAC, or an agency-approved sketch tool).
- **Cost-effectiveness** — total project cost divided by total
  lifetime kilograms reduced, expressed in USD per kilogram. Lower is
  more favorable in every CMAQ cycle.
- **Eligibility category** — the Reference Guide category the project
  falls under (for example, *transit service / expansion*, *diesel
  retrofit*, *travel demand management*, *active transportation*).
- **Nonattainment or maintenance area designation** — the EPA-
  designated area whose air-quality plan the reduction is credited to.

ClawModeler does not synthesize CMAQ inputs. When the lead agency has
not yet staged the `cmaq_overlay.csv` sidecar (long format: one row
per project × pollutant), candidates are not represented in the
estimates table; the portfolio count still reflects total candidates.

